  "text": "We then examined the regulation of acs-2 expression via the use of an acs-2p::GFP reporter gene [CITATION_1] . Treatment of worms carrying the reporter with ALA produced an increase in fluorescence, particularly in the worm intestine (Fig. 1D,F) . The increase in GFP fluorescence was produced via the activation of nhr-49, because treatment with nhr-49 RNAi blocked the increase produced by ALA treatment (Fig. 1D,F) . This activation of nhr-49 also played an important role in the increase in lifespan produced by ALA treatment because nhr-49 RNAi also greatly reduced the effects of ALA treatment on lifespan ( Fig. 1G and Table S1 , Supporting information).",
